Brenda Coons has been in multifamily for over 25 years and is currently the Director of Marketing for Edward Rose & Sons. She oversees the strategic integrated marketing operations of her divisional portfolio including new development assets and sales training and specializes in asset trouble shooting. She has won numerous awards for her innovative marketing programs and collateral materials. She is an NAAEI Certified Instructor and has served as a speaker at various conferences including National Multi-Housing World and National Multi-Housing Council. Brenda is formerly the National Marketing Director of the Gene B. Glick Company. She is an advocate of IAA and has served on several committees including chair of the IAA conference in 1997 and 2007, the Board of Directors, the education committee and is a past recipient of Volunteer of the Year.